Date: 0/0/1921
Source:
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: J of Ag May 20. 313 The introduction of winged thistle (Carduus pycnocephalus) is to be recommended, as it affords both feed for stock and shelter for other plants that may chance to establish. The sowing of cocksfoot, yarrow, wild white clover, and Poa pratensis is to be recommended after the winged thistle has established itself.
